==What is Openttd.cfg?==

Openttd.cfg is the configuration file which OpenTTD uses to store all its settings. You can edit the file using Notepad or any Text Editor.

==How does it work?==

Each time you quit OpenTTD, it writes any changes to the cfg file.
The file has all the variables organised into groups to make it easier to edit.

The groups are
*<nowiki>[misc]</nowiki>
*<nowiki>[win32]</nowiki>
*<nowiki>[music]</nowiki>
*<nowiki>[gameopt]</nowiki>
*<nowiki>[patches]</nowiki>
*<nowiki>[newgrf]</nowiki>
*<nowiki>[network]</nowiki>
*<nowiki>[servers]</nowiki>
*<nowiki>[currency]</nowiki>
*<nowiki>[ban]</nowiki>